-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                              General Information
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Media Info :
Length..............: 1h31mn
Video Format........: H264/AVC (CRF:18)
Video...............: 1280x720 ( 24.976fps )
Bitrate.............: 2700Kbps
Audio...............: AC3 (Constant 192Kbps, 2 channels)
Source..............: JYK's 720p release
IMDB................: http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0829150/

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                 Release Notes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This is a transcode of JYK's release which corrects two issues:
1. Frame rate has been restored to the movie's original FILM rate at 24.976
   fps, thus [almost] eliminating any video stuttering during playback.
2. Black levels (shadows) have been restored through curved channel adjustment,
   which make the picture crisper and a lot less washed out compared to the
   original release.

The audio is the original untouched stream from the source.

Note:
The frame rate reduction was performed using an adaptive algorithm, which made 
it possible nearly perfectly restore the original frame rate, but it's not 
perfect as whomever did the original conversion from FILM to 40 FPS did an 
imperfect job (missing some frames). As such, every now and then you might 
notice a slight skip in the motion. However seeing as the movie alternates 
between very static scenes and high action, you'll likely only notice such 
skips during smooth camera motion, such as when the camera pans a scene (a 
couple of those in here).

Why:
I almost gave up on watching the original due to the &quot;jerky&quot; motion, but 
thought better of it and want to share the result with those who may not have
image or video processing as a hobby, and thus would were stuck to suffer the
original release until a real BR release becomes available.

